  "enhanced_information": "In acute angle closure glaucoma, rapid reduction of intraocular pressure is critical. Pilocarpine, a miotic agent, effectively increases aqueous humor outflow and is indicated for this condition. In contrast, Clozapine, Fluphenazine, and Paroxetine are not indicated for glaucoma treatment as they do not lower intraocular pressure. Clozapine and Fluphenazine are antipsychotics, while Paroxetine is an SSRI, all of which lack efficacy in managing intraocular pressure. Therefore, the drugs that should not be given in this scenario include Clozapine, Fluphenazine, and Paroxetine."
